{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, when a smaller model is required for edge inference, one can train it from a random initialisation, or slice from a teacher as does MLFS, and train starting from the sliced weights.",
    "The latter significantly reduces training time as seen in the validation loss curves.",
    "We see the same benefit on Codellama, as shown below.",
    "See [30] for a similar observation.0 10000 20000 30000 40000 50000 Iteration 1.0 1.5 2.0 2.5 3.0 3.5 4.0 4.5 Validation lossFull FT + random init.",
    "MLFS ( =0, r=8) MLFS ( =0.9, r=8) Results on CodeLlama-7B-Python Here, we experiment on fine-tuning custom smaller models of different sizes using the CodeLlama-7B-Python model as the teacher."
  ]
}